ASISAT Oshoala scored a first-half hat-trick for Barcelona Femeni this season in their 4-0 mauling of Real Betis in a Spanish Primera Iberdrola encounter. After failing to score in her last three home games for the Blaugranes, Oshoala rediscovered her scoring touch at the Johan Cruyff Stadium on Saturday. The former Arsenal and Liverpool forward opened the scoring for the hosts in the 18th minute after benefitting from Caroline Hansen’s assist and she doubled the lead in the 36th minute.   First female FA agent Dora Kayode dedicates excellence award…     JIMMY ABDOU: Meet Comoros’ legendary player who’s among…     AHMED MUSA: Retirement can wait till after World Cup…   It did not stop there for Oshoala who grabbed her third goal for Barcelona with just a minute left before half-time and Fridolina Rolfo sealed the win in the 66th minute. Four minutes later, the Nigeria international was replaced by Jenni Hermoso as Jonatan Giraldez’s side remain unbeaten in the Spanish top-flight. - Advertisement - The 27-year-old has now scored 15 goals in 12 league appearances for Barcelona this term, five goals from equaling her best scoring season in the Primera Iberdrola.